250 g Ground Turkey
½ cup White Cheddar Cheese, shredded
28 g Crispy Shallots
113 g Sugar Snap Peas
340 g Butternut Squash, cubes
1 tsp Garlic Salt
1 unit(s) Red Onion
4 tsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Trim snap peas.
Peel, then cut onion into 1/2-inch pieces, then finley chop 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) onion.
Add snap peas, 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic salt and pepper to a small bowl, then toss to combine. Set aside.

Add squash, 1/2-inch onion pieces and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle the of oven until veggies begins to soften, 10-12 min.
Toss squash, then add snap peas to the baking sheet. Return to the oven and roast until veggies are tender, 10-12 mins.

Meanwhile, add turkey, finely chopped onion and half the crispy shallots to a large bowl. Season with 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic salt and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) pepper, then combine.
Form turkey mixture into six 1/2-inch-thick patties (12 patties for 4 ppl).

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, add patties to the dry pan. Cook on one side until golden-brown, 3-4 min.
Flip patties, then top with cheese. Cover and cook until patties are cooked through and cheese is melted, 3-4 min.**

Sprinkle remaining crispy shallots over cheesy patties. (TIP: Press lightly to stick!)
Divide veggies and patties between plates.

If you've opted to get turkey, prep and cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to prep and cook the pork.**